Storing paths to the data:

In [6]:
def get_labels(dir,random_state=0):
    data_path = []
    data_labels = []
    for label in os.listdir(train_dir):
        label_dir = os.path.join(train_dir, label)
        
        for image in os.listdir(label_dir):
            image_path = os.path.join(label_dir, image)
            data_path.append(image_path)
            data_labels.append(label)

    if shuffle:
        data_path, data_labels = shuffle(data_path, data_labels,random_state=random_state)
    return data_path, data_labels

We can see that the amount of negative space often varies significantly by image. To rectify this in order to maximize accuracy of our algorithm, we can resize the images to make them more standard.

In [18]:
def crop(image):
    im_np = img_to_array(image)
    # Separate brain image from background
    mask = np.any(im_np > 10, axis=2)
    coords = np.argwhere(mask)
    if coords.size == 0:
        return im
    y_min, x_min = coords.min(axis=0)
    y_max, x_max = coords.max(axis=0)
    cropped_np = im_np[y_min:y_max+1, x_min:x_max+1]
    return cropped_np

Modelling¶

In [30]:
model = keras.Sequential()

model.add(InputLayer(shape=(150,150,3)))
model.add(Conv2D(32, (4, 4), activation="relu"))
model.add(MaxPool2D(pool_size=(3, 3)))

model.add(Conv2D(64, (4, 4), activation="relu"))
model.add(MaxPool2D(pool_size=(3, 3)))

model.add(Conv2D(128, (4, 4), activation="relu"))
model.add(MaxPool2D(pool_size=(3, 3)))

model.add(Conv2D(128, (4, 4), activation="relu"))
model.add(Flatten())

model.add(Dense(512, activation="relu"))
model.add(Dropout(0.5, seed=123))
model.add(Dense(4, activation="softmax"))
